{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The wait time between retries doubles with each consecutive failure, up to a configured maximum.","required_reality_check_level":"Unit","justification":"This is backoff math/state progression logic at a local function/object boundary. MOCK-MISS is low if the test directly exercises consecutive-failure counters and max-cap behavior. No REAL-INFRA, LLM-DEP, or MULTI-STEP triggers are present. Rejection gate: higher levels were rejected because the behavior text only specifies deterministic timing calculation, not module handoff or real external effects.","test_description":"Call the backoff calculator (or retry-state object) with failure counts 1..N and assert delays follow 2^k growth capped at configured max.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The retry logic correctly identifies a rate-limit response and computes the appropriate wait time before the next attempt.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure can appear in module interaction: response classification + retry policy + delay computation. A pure unit of either piece can pass while wiring fails (MOCK-MISS). REAL-INFRA is not explicitly required by behavior text; this can be validated with in-process HTTP stubs/fixtures. No LLM-DEP or MULTI-STEP.","test_description":"Wire retry middleware/policy with a stub transport returning a 429-style response (and optional retry-after metadata), then assert it is classified as rate-limit and the computed next-wait value is correct.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"After the wait, the client actually resends the original request and returns the successful result to the caller transparently.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This requires verifying orchestration across timer/backoff + request executor + result propagation, which unit-only tests of isolated pieces can miss. No explicit SYSTEM TRIAD requirement for real external contract/infra is stated; in-process stub transport and controlled timers can expose this behavior. No LLM-DEP or MULTI-STEP.","test_description":"Using fake timers and a stub transport (first response rate-limited, second success), assert the second attempt is sent with equivalent request payload and `call()` resolves to the success value.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After the configured maximum number of retries, the client returns a typed `QuotaExhaustedError` rather than a generic error.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Typed error outcome depends on retry-loop termination and error mapping across components, not just one local mapper. Integration avoids false confidence from isolated unit tests. No explicit real OS/network/subprocess need, no AI dependency, no multi-agent pipeline.","test_description":"Run the retry stack with a stub transport that always returns rate-limit failures; after max retries, assert rejection is instance/type `QuotaExhaustedError` with expected metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full retry chain — initial call, backoff retries, quota tracking — terminates correctly and does not loop indefinitely before surfacing the error.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is an end-to-end local state-machine/orchestration check across multiple modules (retry controller, quota tracker, termination condition). Unit-only tests can miss loop/termination defects in composition. REAL-INFRA is not explicitly required; can be proven with bounded attempts and fake timers in-process. No LLM-DEP or MULTI-STEP agentic sequence.","test_description":"Execute `call()` with persistent rate-limit stub responses, advance timers, and assert total attempts/retry duration remain bounded and final error surfaces without unbounded loop.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Requests issued concurrently from multiple async callers in the same process all draw from the same shared quota bucket.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Concurrency/shared-state correctness is a multi-module interaction concern (scheduler + quota bucket + client instances) and is a classic MOCK-MISS for unit-only tests. No explicit requirement for real external infrastructure; same-process async contention can be tested in-process. No LLM-DEP or agentic workflow.","test_description":"Launch multiple concurrent `call()` invocations against a shared client/account context with controlled stub responses; assert aggregate token/attempt accounting reflects one shared bucket rather than per-caller buckets.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.86,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When multiple requests are waiting to be sent, they are dispatched in the order they were originally submitted.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"FIFO dispatch is queue-orchestration behavior across submission, waiting, and dispatcher modules; unit tests of queue primitive alone can miss integration ordering bugs. No explicit SYSTEM TRIAD trigger requiring real network/OS verification. No LLM-DEP or multi-agent chain.","test_description":"Submit several async calls rapidly into a constrained qu